    <string name="tutorial_step_intro_title">Hello~ I\'m Senni</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_intro_body">I float over your other apps so we can chat anytime~ The next few screens are my little gesture school — everything here is live, so don\'t be shy.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_tap_title">Tap me to walk</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_tap_body">Give me a tap and I\'ll stroll across the screen. Go on, try it~</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_escape_title">Pester me and I\'ll bolt</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_escape_body">Keep tapping and I get startled — I\'ll dash off one edge and sneak back in from the other. See if you can make me run~</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_talk_title">Hold me to talk</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_talk_body">Long-press my upper body and I\'ll listen 🎙 — just speak, and I\'ll answer out loud. If capture is on (flip it in my quick menu), I\'ll also grab your screen or snap a photo so you can ask about what we\'re looking at.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_recall_title">Missed what I said?</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_recall_body">Long-press my lower body and I\'ll bring my last reply back. Dismiss it, or type a follow-up right there~</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_radial_title">Swipe up: my quick menu</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_radial_body">Swipe up on me for my settings dial — capture mode, the volume-button shortcut, and my voice. Swipe down (or tap away) to close it.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_visibility_title">Need me out of sight?</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_visibility_body">Double-press Volume Down and I\'ll hide; double-press again and I\'m back~ Try it on the volume key at the edge.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_voice_title">Talk to me hands-free</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_voice_body">Triple-press Volume Down or press an assistant button and I\'m listening — no screen tap needed. I\'ll echo what I heard 🎙, think 🧠, and answer aloud. Give the edge key three quick presses~</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_tools_title">I can search &amp; use tools</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_tools_body">Ask about current events and my Nexus brain searches the web and uses its tools — watch for my 🔧 badge. Tap me to replay~</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_ghost_title">I won\'t block your typing</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_ghost_body">When a keyboard pops up I turn ghostly and let your taps pass right through me. Bring up the keyboard and press a few keys — right through me~</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_outro_title">That\'s everything~</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_outro_body">Tap me to walk, hold me to talk or recall, swipe up for my menu. I\'ll be floating right here whenever you need me. Have fun~ ✨</string>
    <string name="tutorial_recall_placeholder">This is where my last reply would appear!</string>
    <string name="tutorial_canned_response">Ooh, a code editor~ Looks like you\'re deep in a Kotlin file. Want me to explain what\'s on screen, or just keep you company?</string>
    <string name="tutorial_canned_followup">Got it! That\'s exactly how a real reply works — I\'d read it and answer. Try the next gesture when you\'re ready. ✨</string>
    <string name="tutorial_canned_voice_reply">You said that out loud and I heard you~ This very reply is my on-device voice — no internet required. Handy when you\'d rather talk than type.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_canned_search_reply">It\'s sunny and 72 degrees~ That came from a weather tool. In the real app I can call tools and search the web for you.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_senni_label" translatable="false">SENNI</string>
    <string name="tutorial_intro_spoken">Hello~ I\'m Senni! Let me show you around.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_outro_spoken">And that\'s everything! Have fun out there~</string>

